{
  "texts": [
    "As Figures 2b and 3d illustrate, the similarity scores are significantly lower compared to the other 5 metrics.",
    "This difference primarily arises from our method of calculating the metric.",
    "Specifically, the similarity score is determined by averaging the scores of all paired polymers between the training and generated sets, which assess whether the generative model accurately represents the distribution of the existing data.",
    "To benchmark these values, we calculated two baseline scores: first, the similarity between two identical polymer datasets (HTP-MD datasets).",
    "Second, the similarity between the HTP-MD dataset and the PI1M dataset."
  ]
}